Harbor Docker

Harbor Docker is a backend project built with FastAPI, SQLAlchemy, Alembic, PostgreSQL, and Docker. The project focuses on database design,
 ORM modeling, Docker constraints and REST API development rather than frontend development.

Current Features
Dockerized PostgreSQL database
SQLAlchemy ORM models
Alembic database migrations
Harbor management schema including:
Captains
Ships
Harbors
Docks
Docking records
PostgreSQL constraints, relationships, and enums

Planned Features
REST API endpoints with FastAPI
CRUD operations for all entities
Pydantic request and response schemas
Business logic for ship docking and harbor operations
Validation and error handling
Dockerized API service with Docker Compose

Tech Stack
Python 3.12
FastAPI
SQLAlchemy
Alembic
PostgreSQL
Docker
Project Goals

This project is intended to strengthen backend development skills by focusing on:

Relational database design
SQLAlchemy ORM
Database migrations with Alembic
Docker-based development
REST API architecture
Clean backend project structure

This project will funcon as a ship gide showing captens where ships can go based on cargo time 